pullRequest.title: Fixes #6903
pullRequest.bodyText:
Fixes #6903
Seems that in this case, the overriding of remove was not detected, because for a List<>; it thought I used
remove(Object) instead of the expected remove(long)
The second interesting thing here is that the class CardQueue was added last minute, and not tested in my merge branch
as the remaining of the PR.

nodes.bodyText: yessss! love seeing a test for it that pokes the problem
Optional: you could implement the interface to remove this method. Likely not worth it
Didn't we add getFirstCard for situations like this? Could save a little time per test
Java naming standards, and could do with a more descriptive name
Note.cards() is slow, factor it into one call

beforeCommit.message: NF: encapsulate list in card queue

commit.message:
NF: use correct type

Seems that in this case, the overriding of `remove` was not detected, because for a `List<>`; it thought I used
`remove(Object)` instead of the expected `remove(long)`

The second interesting thing here is that the class CardQueue was added last minute, and not tested in my merge branch
as the remaining of the PR.
NF: encapsulate list in card queue
